  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pf-section-label">FORMBY PROPERTY KNOWLEDGE</span>
      <h2>Is Your Formby Home Getting the Full Annual Service It Actually Needs?</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">A standard 45-minute combi boiler service is not sufficient for many of Formby's larger properties. Here is what a complete annual service looks like for L37's most common heating configurations.</p>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem;">

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">COMBI</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Standard Combi Service. 45 to 60 Minutes.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">For smaller Formby properties with a single bathroom and a combi boiler, the standard annual service covers combustion gas analysis, gas pressure and flow rate, burner and heat exchanger inspection, flue integrity check, safety device testing, system pressure check, inhibitor test and top-up, magnetic filter clean and full function test. Benchmark updated and service certificate emailed same day. This is correct and complete for a single-zone combi boiler property.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card pf-card-left-orange">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--orange);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">SYSTEM</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">System Boiler Service. 60 to 75 Minutes. Same Price.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0;line-height:1.65;">System boilers are common in Formby's 3 to 5 bedroom properties and are paired with hot water cylinders. A complete system boiler service includes everything in the combi service plus zone valve testing and operation, pump condition and flow assessment, motorised valve function and timing, cylinder thermostat accuracy check, expansion vessel pressure verification and all heating circuit zone controls. For properties with underfloor heating zones, each zone circuit and its controls is checked. Engineers who primarily service combi boilers may not carry out these additional checks, or may attempt to charge extra for them. We include them at the same £120 fixed price.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pf-card" style="border-top:4px solid var(--navy);">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <div style="background:var(--navy);color:#fff;border-radius:6px;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:0.85rem;white-space:nowrap;flex-shrink:0;">CYLINDER</div>
            <div>
              <strong style="display:block;color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.35rem;">Unvented Cylinder Annual Check. A Legal Requirement That Many Formby Homeowners Miss.</strong>
              <p style="font-size:0.93rem;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 0.75rem;line-height:1.65;">If your Formby home has an unvented hot water cylinder, also known as a mains pressure cylinder, it requires an annual safety inspection that is separate from your boiler service. This is not optional and it is not the same as a boiler service. The annual cylinder check must be carried out by a G3 qualified engineer and covers the pressure relief valve condition and operation, expansion vessel pressure, temperature and pressure relief valve integrity, thermostat accuracy, immersion heater condition and overall cylinder integrity. Failure to have this inspection carried out annually can void your cylinder warranty and, more importantly, means you have no professional confirmation that these safety components are operating correctly.</p>
              <div style="background:#eff6ff;border:1px solid #bfdbfe;border-radius:var(--radius-sm);padding:0.75rem 1rem;">
