        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">SYSTEM BOILER</span>&nbsp; Do you service system boilers in Formby at the same price?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. We service system boilers at the same £120 fixed price as combi boilers. The system boiler service includes zone valve testing, pump condition check, expansion vessel pressure, motorised valve function and all heating circuit controls in addition to the standard boiler checks. We allow more time for system boiler visits and carry zone valve and pump spares on every van.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">G3</span>&nbsp; Are you G3 qualified to service unvented cylinders in Formby?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All our engineers hold G3 qualification for unvented cylinder work. This is a legal requirement for working on mains pressure hot water systems. G3 qualification is also required to service, inspect and certify the safety components on unvented cylinders. We carry out the cylinder annual inspection alongside the boiler service in a single visit across Formby L37.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">BENCHMARK</span>&nbsp; Does the Formby service include a Benchmark update?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. We update the Benchmark commissioning record on every service visit. This is required by Worcester Bosch, Vaillant and other manufacturers to maintain warranty validity. Service certificate and cylinder inspection record both emailed the same day.</p></div></details>
